Overcast- level highest yet this summer.  Rainfall from 7/7-7/10 was 3.5".
Cloudy- kind of gloomy day.  Slight chop on water- and overcast like a fall day.  The rainfall from 7/10-8/20 is 2.5 inches.
Sunny- choppy- 72 F- some algae bloom- level high.
Slight. algae bloom close to shore.  The rainfall from 8/20-9/19 was 6.6 inches.  The air temperature is 52 degrees F.
Light clouds- the temperature is 36 degrees F- very cold.  The rainfall from 9/19-10/22 is 3.5".

Partly sunny- windy- no more rain.

Bloom present- but two inches of rainfall and winds cleared the pond scum (algae) out.
Bloom present- south end.  Calm- sunny- 60 degrees.

50 degrees F- sunny- clear.  Rain gauge from 6/27 to 7/25 is 3.75 inches.
About 8 inches of rain since 9/12- warm bloom present.

Inch of rain night before.  Choppy.

Partly sunny.  Some white caps.  North wind 39 F.
Sunny.  Dead calm.  Algae on surface.

flat water- algae scum layer on surface
past week of below average temps cooled water down significantly.
There were more loons on the lake than usual this morning- I counted 8 versus the usual 2 or 3.  The lake is starting to turn over.  Slight skim of algae on surface.

Some algae noticed in the water as well as some pollen on the surface.  High winds last night did damage to trees and some docks as well.  The water really got mixed up with the big waves as is evident in the data.
